# nclawzero-rescue / authorized_keys.example
#
# THIS FILE IS COMMITTED.  Documents the format the rescue initramfs
# (nclawzero-rescue-init recipe) expects at /root/.ssh/authorized_keys.
# The actual fleet key list lives in a sibling file `authorized_keys`
# (no .example suffix) which is gitignored — never published.
#
# Convention: keep this in lockstep with
#   recipes-core/nclawzero-ssh-keys/files/authorized_keys
# so a Jetson that PXE-boots into rescue and one that boots its
# production rootfs accept the same operator pubkeys. Rotation edits
# both files at the same time, as described in
# nclawzero-rescue-init_1.0.bb's recipe header.
#
# Same format as the ssh-keys file (see that file's .example for full
# notes). Both contexts use root-only access in rescue (rescue is
# stateless / ephemeral) but ncz + jasonperlow on the production rootfs.
#
# To populate before building the rescue initramfs:
#
#   cp recipes-core/nclawzero-rescue/files/authorized_keys.example \
#      recipes-core/nclawzero-rescue/files/authorized_keys
#   $EDITOR recipes-core/nclawzero-rescue/files/authorized_keys

# Replace these placeholder lines with real fleet workstation keys:
ssh-ed25519 AAAAREPLACEME jperlow@<workstation-name>
# ssh-ed25519 AAAAREPLACEME <user>@<host>
